articles.author: Jonathan Stempel
articles.description: Alphabet's Google (GOOGL.O) has agreed to settle a lawsuit claiming it secretly tracked the internet use of millions of people who thought they were doing their browsing privately.
articles.title: Google settles $5 billion consumer privacy lawsuit

articles.author: Mrinmay Dey
articles.description: Elon Musk's X on Thursday failed to block a California state law that requires social media companies to publicly disclose how they moderate certain content on their platforms.
articles.title: Elon Musk's X fails to block California's content moderation law

articles.author: Chen Aizhu, Oksana Kobzeva
articles.description: U.S. sanctions pose a major obstacle to Russia's plans to increase exports of seaborne liquefied natural gas (LNG) to offset the decline in pipeline gas exports to Europe, analysts said, as expectations mount of delays to a flagship project.
articles.title: Russia faces mighty obstacle in western LNG sanctions

articles.author: Stephen Culp
articles.description: Wall Street drifted higher in light trading on Thursday, as firming bets of interest rate cuts in the coming year supported stock prices as market participants eyed a potential bull market confirmation.
articles.title: Wall St inches higher as S&P 500 flirts with bull market confirmation

articles.author: Chen Chen Lin
articles.description: Singapore households are bracing for a sales tax hike that takes effect in the new year as the government shores up coffers ahead of an expected surge in social spending in the rapidly ageing city-state in the years ahead.
articles.title: Singapore readies sales tax hike as demographic crunch looms

articles.author: Andrew Goudsward
articles.description: Maine on Thursday disqualified Donald Trump from the state ballot in next year’s U.S. presidential primary election, becoming the second state to bar the former president for his role in the Jan. 6, 2021, attack on the U.S. Capitol.
articles.title: Maine elections official disqualifies Trump from presidential primary ballot

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Bassam Masoud
articles.description: Israeli forces attacked areas of the central and southern Gaza Strip where residents have been expecting a renewed ground offensive in areas crammed with tens of thousands of Palestinians already displaced by the Israeli-Hamas war.
articles.title: Israeli tanks, missiles strike Gaza in offensive against Hamas

articles.author: Phil Stewart, David Latona, Angelo Amante
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden hoped to present a firm international response to Yemen's Houthi attacks on Red Sea shipping by launching a new maritime force, but a week after its launch many allies don't want to be associated with it, publicly, or at all.
articles.title: US allies reluctant on Red Sea task force

articles.author: Rupam Jain
articles.description: Vishnu Dabad attributes his rise from poverty to powerful local politician to an animal: the cow.
articles.title: India's far-right cow vigilantes bolster clout before high-stake elections

articles.author: Joey Roulette, Steve Gorman
articles.description: The U.S. military's secretive X-37B robot spaceplane blasted off from Florida on Thursday night on its seventh mission, the first launched atop a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket capable of delivering it to a higher orbit than ever before.
articles.title: US military's secretive spaceplane launched on possible higher-orbit mission
